want me to risk it.

819
00:49:43,247 --> 00:49:44,580
At the end of it all,

820
00:49:44,748 --> 00:49:46,427
I'm gonna have
to work like a dog

821
00:49:46,451 --> 00:49:47,984
for the rest of the semester

822
00:49:48,152 --> 00:49:50,431
just to catch up on
my other classes.

823
00:49:50,455 --> 00:49:53,155
You have described
your difficulties,

824
00:49:53,324 --> 00:49:59,161
but you haven't answered
my question of why.

825
00:49:59,330 --> 00:50:00,662
I don't know.

826
00:50:00,831 --> 00:50:04,766
I just... I think of
Jesus as my friend.

827
00:50:05,136 --> 00:50:09,305
<i>So, you think Jesus is God?</i>

828
00:50:09,474 --> 00:50:11,640
Yeah, and the Son of God.

829
00:50:11,809 --> 00:50:13,487
I don't want to disappoint him,

830
00:50:13,511 --> 00:50:17,013
even if everyone
thinks I should.

831
00:50:17,181 --> 00:50:21,250
See, to me, he's not dead.

832
00:50:21,419 --> 00:50:24,420
He's alive.

833
00:50:24,588 --> 00:50:26,988
I don't want anyone to get
talked out of believing in him

834
00:50:27,125 --> 00:50:31,627
just because some
professor thinks they should.

835
00:50:37,201 --> 00:50:39,301
See you around, Martin.

836
00:50:39,470 --> 00:50:41,803
Bye.

837
00:50:54,218 --> 00:50:57,053
Hiya, Tom Blanchard,
Metro City Auto.

838
00:50:57,221 --> 00:50:58,554
<i>Here's your keys.</i>

839
00:50:58,722 --> 00:51:01,257
- Thank you.
